JOHANNESBURG, January 23 – Free State police are looking for information after the Riebeeckstad Methodist church’s gate was stolen last week. Police spokesperson Captain Stephen Thakeng said the church’s caretaker stated he had locked the gates before leaving the premises last Thursday. “On Friday at about 7am when he arrived at the church he found that the devil fork gate valued at R15 000-00 was missing,” Thakeng said. He said a case docket of theft was registered at Welkom police station but the suspects were still unknown at this stage. – African News Agency (ANA)